flowRoot.flowPara: Can change both the elements and the sequence; elements may be dropped, shifted, duplicated or merged with other sequences
Transforms the elements in the sequence but does not change the sequence order or timing
Does not change neither the elements nor the sequence, but can introduce side-effects
Represents a property of another node. Writing to it at runtime will change the value of the property
A nested combinator uses an internal (nested) dataflow to implement specific operations
Does not change the elements in the sequence but can drop (filter out) elements from the sequence
